1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:12,167
<i> So that means you did all this</i>

2
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:14,233
<i>to give your daughter a present
for her birthday?</i>

3
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,200
<i>I know I won't last long
as a fugitive.</i>

4
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,833
<i>I just really want to visit
my family</i>

5
00:00:17,967 --> 00:00:18,833
<i> on my daughter's birthday.</i>

6
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,033
<i>What are you doing
to our friend?</i>

7
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:23,900
<i> Hey! Hey, come back here!</i>

8
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:25,467
<i>You know, we used to be
like that too.</i>

9
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,867
<i>But we've long accepted
that Tonyo loves someone else.</i>

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,200
<i> Who?</i>

11
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>The beautiful police officer
he works with, Ma'am Bobby.</i>

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:36,000
<i>Major, a tip came in
about Mandong Warak.</i>

13
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>I'm really good
at faking things.</i>

14
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,800
<i>Let's see if they will take
this bait.</i>

15
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,167
<i> No one will engage, okay?</i>

16
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:44,067
<i>Let's just ID him,
then we'll regroup here.</i>

17
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,500
<i> What's going to happen to her?</i>

18
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:50,867
<i>She'll definitely go to jail for
selling the pimple patch drugs.</i>

19
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
<i> Sorry, Monty.</i>

20
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,300
<i> What now?</i>

21
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:54,733
<i>We didn't catch the guy Jhem
was talking to last night.</i>

22
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:56,900
<i>We'll profile him.
It'll be easier to find him.</i>

23
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:58,167
<i> You're so stupid!</i>

24
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:02,433
<i>Monty and his girlfriend
must be killed.</i>

25
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:03,867
<i> Do you understand that?</i>

26
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,467
<i> This won't take long, Boss.</i>

27
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:09,233
<i> I have his love team now.</i>

28
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,267
<i> Bobby?</i>

29
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,533
<i>We won't have any problems,
right?</i>

30
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:13,200
<i> None.</i>

31
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,400
<i> Report to me afterwards.</i>

32
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,633
Nice.

33
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:22,500
By the way, Sir,
can I visit Boss Tonyo?

34
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,800
Sure.

35
00:01:23,933 --> 00:01:26,467
You tell him about
your accomplishment.

36
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,333
I'm sure he'll be happy.

37
00:01:28,467 --> 00:01:29,433
Okay, Sir.

38
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:31,500
What, Bro? Let's use
the bike again?

39
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:34,133
I'll pass on that, Vince.
I'm tired from riding the bike.

40
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:35,700
Maybe I'll just take a cab.

41
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:37,633
Chief, thank you.

42
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:39,500
Take care, thank you.

43
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:40,400
Okay, Sir.

44
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:44,700
What are you doing?

45
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:46,767
What? That was just a fist bump.

46
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,233
You're really crazy.

47
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:00,667
Ma'am Bobby!

48
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:04,033
Ma'am Bobby, negative.
No one's here.

49
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,600
Ma'am Bobby?

50
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,500
Ma'am Bobby?

51
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:30,267
Hello, Noble?

52
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,767
Chief, apologies,
did Ma'am Enriquez contact you?

53
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:34,800
No, why?

54
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:36,633
She suddenly disappeared

55
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:38,400
from the place you asked us
to check.

56
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:40,900
What?

57
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:43,033
How did she disappear?

58
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:44,433
I don't know, Sir.

59
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:45,600
We checked the place separately,

60
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:48,933
and now, I can't find her
anymore.

61
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:35,867
Sir...

62
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,633
here.

63
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:39,867
Here, Sir.

64
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,133
Sergeant Enriquez and I
split up here.

65
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:46,700
I went here.

66
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,533
Sergeant Enriquez went there.

67
00:03:48,667 --> 00:03:50,667
There's no CCTV here either,
Sir.

68
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,533
How will we know what happened
to Sergeant Enriquez?

69
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,933
I'm nervous, Sir.

70
00:03:57,067 --> 00:04:00,333
What if one of the inmates
took her?

71
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,733
Sir, should we inform Sergeant
Enriquez's grandmother?

72
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:05,767
No.

73
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,733
We don't know everything
that's going on yet.

74
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:10,567
How about Lieutenant Conde,
should we tell him?

75
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,233
Not yet.

76
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:14,067
Let him rest for now.

77
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:17,267
Chief is the one we need
to update here.

78
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,267
I'm sure he'll call anytime now.

79
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,833
Go ahead, patrol the area.

80
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:48,000
Let me go.

81
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:49,333
Let me go!

82
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:51,467
Hey!

83
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:59,333
Conde really has a type.

84
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:07,767
You're an animal! Let me go!

85
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:14,367
You're getting hurt already,
but you're still beautiful.

86
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:33,233
Don't worry, Bobby.

87
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,033
I am a professional.

88
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:41,333
Let me go!

89
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:42,767
You're an animal!

90
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,567
Too bad, Boss. I could've
assisted you in peeing.

91
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,633
You're crazy!

92
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:05,267
It's good to have you on board,
Matibag.

93
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,200
It's good that you're here.

94
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:10,167
Vince, how's Mariano doing?

95
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,667
He's in Manila now,

96
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,933
but he said he'll come back
when he can.

97
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,800
It's good that you two
got along.

98
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:18,767
We're okay, Boss.

99
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,600
He's not that arrogant.

100
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:23,533
I'm still more handsome
than him, Bro.

101
00:06:24,867 --> 00:06:27,700
Sir Tonyo, what's our next
assignment?

102
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,633
For now, there's nothing,

103
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:34,700
so you two should rest
because you did a good job.

104
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,500
As for me,

105
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:38,067
I need to rest as well

106
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,933
since I'm allowed to be
discharged tomorrow.

107
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,367
Wait, by the way,

108
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,233
do you have any news about
the fugitives who escaped?

109
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:47,033
About Mandong Warak, Sir?

110
00:06:47,167 --> 00:06:48,667
All I know is that they're still
looking for them.

111
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:52,300
So be careful, okay?

112
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:53,600
Especially you,

113
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:55,867
because we police officers
are in danger

114
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,800
while that jerk is on the loose.

115
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,800
I'll send our picture
to your boyfriend, okay?

116
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:41,133
Bobby?

117
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:42,200
What's that, Boss?

118
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:43,133
It seems like you received
a serious message.

119
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:44,267
Vince, shut up.

120
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,467
Sir Tonyo, what's the problem?

121
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,600
It's Enriquez...

122
00:07:49,467 --> 00:07:50,733
Mandong Warak has her.

123
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:53,433
How did that happen, Boss?

124
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:55,567
Sir, just tell us and we'll get
out of here right away.

125
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:57,733
No, no.

126
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:00,400
I'm the only one
who should do it.

127
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,500
He wants me to be the only one
to face him.

128
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,467
But, Sir, we can just wait
for your signal.

129
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,000
It's dangerous if you go alone.

130
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:07,200
Sir, that's too dangerous.

131
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,333
We'll go with you.

132
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:09,867
Better yet, Sir, I'll report
this to the chief.

133
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,367
No way, Matibag!

134
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,700
I can't risk Bobby's life.

135
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:17,667
Mando has no soul.

136
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,367
He has nothing to lose
if he kills Bobby.

137
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,767
Do you understand that?

138
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:26,167
Do you really want to help me?

139
00:08:28,767 --> 00:08:30,600
There's something
I need you to do.

140
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,200
Where is Matibag?

141
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,700
He just made a call, Boss.

142
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:46,933
What, Boss? Are you sure
you can do it?

143
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:47,767
Yes.

144
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:51,700
There he is.

145
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,233
Sir Tonyo.

146
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,367
Thank you.

147
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:09,433
Sir Tonyo, I'm sorry, but are
you really sure about this?

148
00:09:09,567 --> 00:09:11,067
It's different if there's backup
waiting.

149
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,167
Thanks for your concern,

150
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:16,567
but this is the only way
that I can save Bobby.

151
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,167
<i> Where are you going, Conde?</i>

152
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:22,933
<i>Do you know what you're doing
is extremely dangerous?</i>

153
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:24,533
<i>Why don't you ask for our help?</i>

154
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:32,800
Sir, I'm sorry, but if anyone
really knows Mando, it's me.

155
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:35,467
I know exactly how he works.

156
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:39,600
<i>I understand, Conde,
but you can't do it.</i>

157
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:40,967
<i>You're not fully recovered yet.</i>

158
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:43,267
<i>You and Enriquez might just get
in danger.</i>

159
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:47,000
Sir, I won't let Mando
hurt Bobby.

160
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:50,200
Mando already had many victims.

161
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:54,633
So if you really want to help
me, find the other fugitives.

162
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,833
Let's not let the number
of victims increase

163
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:59,033
because of their escape.

164
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:01,433
<i> Okay, Conde, be careful,</i>

165
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,600
<i> and update me right away.</i>

166
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:04,700
Yes, Sir.

167
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,133
Sir, I'm sorry.

168
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:11,933
Don't follow.

169
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,600
It's your fault, Bro.

170
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:22,100
The manhunt operation continues.

171
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,900
Are you sure, Sir?

172
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:29,333
If Conde thinks this is the best
option to save Enriquez...

173
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:32,067
let's just trust him.

174
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,500
What happened to dad?

175
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:02,000
Well, apparently,

176
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:06,433
your half-sister got abducted
by one of the escapees.

177
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:09,533
Glen...

178
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:14,567
coordinate with Major Flores.

179
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:20,933
Make sure that they get
everything they need.

180
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:28,400
Let's do everything we can
to save your sister, Bobby.

181
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:30,500
Yes, Dad, I'll do that.

182
00:11:30,633 --> 00:11:31,500
I promise.

183
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:38,100
They'll pay if anything happens
to your sister.

184
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:39,733
I won't let that happen.

185
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:03,967
Sir Tonyo is really
something else, Sir.

186
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:06,867
He really went alone
to save Ma'am Bobby.

187
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:10,700
If I were in his situation,
I would do the same.

188
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,700
Do you also have a special
someone too, Sir?

189
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,000
Special someone?

190
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:20,767
Let's not talk about that.

191
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:23,967
By the way, I just want
to tell you, Bautista,

192
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:25,767
that you're very lucky.

193
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,100
Why, Sir Eric?

194
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:31,300
Imagine, of all the people you
could have been partnered with,

195
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:33,000
you were given to me.

196
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:35,567
You can learn a lot from me.

197
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,567
Who are we meeting here, Sir?

198
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,333
This is my lesson to you,
Bautista.

199
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,933
These kinds of fugitives,

200
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:47,900
the first thing they go back to
is their relatives.

201
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:50,967
Well, last night, Sir,

202
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:55,867
we didn't get anything from
going around to their families.

203
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,367
Of course, they're still
chilling.

204
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,733
They won't go there right away,
will they?

205
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,100
In fairness, Sir,
you have a point.

206
00:13:05,233 --> 00:13:05,833
There.

207
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:07,167
That's what I want from you.

208
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,767
You learn quickly.

209
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:09,967
Let's go.

210
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:14,800
Let's go to Sweetie Villanueva,
Edgar Villanueva's wife.

211
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:30,867
<i>Where are you?
I'm getting bored.</i>

212
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,633
<i> I'm on my way.</i>

213
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:42,467
Conde really loves you.

214
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,700
I'm sure his wound
hasn't healed yet,

215
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,567
but I'm still amazed...

216
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:53,333
he really wants to save you.

217
00:13:57,767 --> 00:14:00,967
Your end is near, Conde.

218
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:14,200
Everything that's happened
is really bad, isn't it?

219
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,267
Anika died...

220
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,133
and then Jhem is in jail.

221
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:21,500
It doesn't show in their looks.

222
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:23,533
That's why they can't
catch them.

223
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,533
You know, Bro, I've been hearing

224
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,867
about that pimple patch drugs
here at school for a while now.

225
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:30,433
Bro, sorry,

226
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:33,500
but isn't your brother
a supplier of that, too?

227
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:36,200
Yes, but he sells it
to someone else.

228
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,367
I don't know. I don't care
about him anymore.

229
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,167
Vic!

230
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:42,100
Hey, Bro.

231
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,767
Where's Bill?

232
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,800
He's just taking care
of something.

233
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:51,567
What? Come on. Let's go train.
There's a tournament coming up.

234
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:56,133
Sorry, Bro, but I don't think

235
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:58,067
I'll be able to join your
taekwondo team anymore.

236
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,367
What do you mean?
You just tried out.

237
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:05,200
Come on, Bro. I have something
to tell you.

238
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:16,533
That truth is,
we just came in here

239
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:18,967
to solve the case about the
pimple patch drug selling.

240
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:21,667
What?

241
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,133
So are you a secret agent?
Is that it?

242
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:25,600
Undercover, Bro.

243
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:30,167
Sorry, but we only joined
your team

244
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:33,300
because we thought you were
the one selling the patches.

245
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:34,900
Because Monty is my brother?

246
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,567
Sorry, Bro.

247
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,500
I hope you understand.
It's just work.

248
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,967
What's your real name?

249
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,033
Vince.

250
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:48,500
And my partner, Will,
he's a cop.

251
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,433
Nice to meet you, Vince.

252
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,400
You're really something else,
aren't you?

253
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:55,800
Thanks, Bro.

254
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:08,333
You can't get out of there.

255
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:11,633
Hey...

256
00:16:11,767 --> 00:16:13,967
your boyfriend sent a message.

257
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,867
He said he's on his way.

258
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,333
Let me just meet him, okay?

259
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,800
Just stay there.

260
00:16:23,967 --> 00:16:26,467
And after I kill him...

261
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,967
I'll take you to heaven.

262
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:35,700
You animal!

263
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,400
You have no shame!

264
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:47,800
What really happened?

265
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:49,967
How did Jhem get involved
in this?

266
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,500
As it turned out,

267
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:57,133
Jhem was really the supplier
here at school.

268
00:16:57,267 --> 00:17:02,233
Anika was just a user.
She just got involved.

269
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:05,367
You know, drugs are really
a dirty business.

270
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,600
So do Vic and Bill have anything
to do with this?

271
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:09,900
Vince.

272
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:11,767
Vince is my real name.

273
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,633
The guy I'm with,
his real name is Will.

274
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,567
He's a cop.

275
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:17,800
What?

276
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:19,000
What are you?

277
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:22,667
Undercover?

278
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:26,200
Yes, Jade.

279
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:30,000
You know about it, Faye?

280
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:32,667
Yes, but it's a secret.

281
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,867
Will wanted to say goodbye,

282
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,867
but he needed to take care
of something in Manila.

283
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,633
Yes, Vince, we understand.

284
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:42,767
Your job here is done anyway.

285
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,433
We'll see each other again,
right?

286
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:48,900
I'll contact the vice mayor.

287
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:51,933
Maybe he can offer us some work.

288
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:53,700
Okay, please.

289
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:56,800
Vince, thanks for your help.

290
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:59,467
The ending wasn't great, but...

291
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,067
at least, the sale
of pimple patch drugs

292
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,533
has stopped here at school.

293
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:08,467
Thanks for your help too,
Faye and Jade.

294
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,000
So, I'll go ahead.

295
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,300
<i> Just stay there, Tonyo.</i>

296
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,167
<i> Put down your gun.</i>

297
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,467
<i> I said, put down your gun!</i>

298
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:19,967
Mando...

299
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:23,467
I'm the one who wronged you.

300
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:27,500
Let Enriquez go.

301
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:29,633
You're talking too much.

302
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:32,700
Are you really trying
to push me now?

303
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:36,767
You know I can kill
your love team.

304
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,567
Lift up your clothes.

305
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,633
Lift it up.

306
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:43,633
Maybe you're still carrying
something there.

307
00:20:48,967 --> 00:20:50,400
Hey, hey...

308
00:20:50,533 --> 00:20:52,167
How's your wound?

309
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:53,633
Does that still hurt?

310
00:20:53,767 --> 00:20:54,933
Let's check.

311
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,700
Sorry, sorry, sorry, sorry.

312
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:03,833
It still hurts. I'm sorry.

313
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:23,067
What?

314
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,400
Are you happy now?

315
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,400
Let Bobby go.

316
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:30,400
Not yet.

317
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,633
I still want to play with you.

318
00:21:37,167 --> 00:21:38,133
Put that on.

319
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:42,167
I said, put that on!

320
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:45,267
Hurry up.

321
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:03,900
What? Remember when you
handcuffed me?

322
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,933
When you ruined my face?

323
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:12,267
That's not enough for the number
of police officers you killed.

324
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,200
Why?

325
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:16,567
We're just the same.

326
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:20,100
Police officers like you
and criminals like us.

327
00:22:21,467 --> 00:22:23,800
The difference is that
you don't get acquitted.

328
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:27,167
Not all police officers are bad.

329
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:30,267
But I haven't met a police
officer who isn't bad.

330
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,867
So that's right.

331
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,933
Everyone I killed
deserved to be killed.

332
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:40,400
You're the next one on my list.

333
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:46,933
Our attack here should be
for interrogation.

334
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:50,533
Who we're going to talk to
are the fugitives' relatives.

335
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:55,567
We need to determine if what
they're saying is true or not.

336
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,667
Roman, has Mando
updated you yet?

337
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,100
I've been calling him
for a while now,

338
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:00,000
but he's not answering.

339
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:00,767
Glen.

340
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:03,333
Let's play hide-and-seek first.

341
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:04,867
If I catch you,

342
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:11,000
I'll chop you up finely
while your love team watches.

343
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:13,900
Then, I'll kill her next.

344
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:15,667
Goodbye, Conde.
